WEBVTT

00:01.701 --> 00:06.139
♪♪

00:06.206 --> 00:09.642
♪ I like that, yeah ♪

00:09.709 --> 00:11.244
♪ I like that ♪

00:11.344 --> 00:13.847
♪♪

00:13.913 --> 00:15.248
It's my job
as your debate teacher

00:15.348 --> 00:16.883
to try to get you
to think outside the box,

00:16.983 --> 00:18.418
so think about it this way.

00:18.518 --> 00:20.920
Would you rather own
a tropical island --

00:21.021 --> 00:23.323
Island.
I want to own an island.

00:23.390 --> 00:24.824
You didn't let me finish.

00:24.891 --> 00:26.159
Would you rather own an island

00:26.226 --> 00:28.728
or donate those billions
to Feeding America?

00:28.828 --> 00:31.531
Well, I've already committed
to the island thing, so...

00:31.598 --> 00:34.934
I'm also for Luke
moving to an island by himself,

00:35.035 --> 00:36.936
far away
from everyone.

00:37.037 --> 00:38.438
[ Chatter, knock on door ]

00:38.538 --> 00:40.340
Sorry to interrupt.
Quick question.

00:40.407 --> 00:42.509
Anyone interested in starring
in a production

00:42.575 --> 00:46.613
of the greatest alien love story
of all time --

00:46.713 --> 00:49.549
"As the World Sa-Turns"?

00:49.616 --> 00:52.452
It's my original piece
I am writing and directing

00:52.552 --> 00:55.889
for our school's annual musical
in a week.

00:55.955 --> 00:57.290
Who's in?

00:57.390 --> 00:58.458
Oh,
I would say yes,

00:58.558 --> 01:00.427
but my mom
told me to stop lying.

01:00.527 --> 01:02.595
Quick question --
[ Chuckles ]

01:02.695 --> 01:04.898
could I join,
do very little work,

01:04.964 --> 01:07.867
take very much credit,
and put it on my college résumé?

01:07.934 --> 01:09.536
Super smart idea --

01:09.602 --> 01:12.806
which is why
I'm already doing it.

01:12.906 --> 01:14.140
So I have a quesh.

01:14.240 --> 01:15.408
No,
teachers can't audition.

01:15.475 --> 01:16.776
Hey, but could they
if they sang

01:16.876 --> 01:19.746
a showstopping ballad
like "Chandelier" by Sia?

01:19.813 --> 01:21.047
Oh, I wish,
but rules are rules.

01:21.114 --> 01:22.482
Too bad
it's just for students.

01:22.582 --> 01:23.983
Ah, damn it.

01:24.084 --> 01:26.119
I would have
been amazing.

01:26.219 --> 01:39.399
♪♪

01:39.466 --> 01:46.406
♪ I'm gonna swing
from the chandelier ♪

01:46.473 --> 01:50.343
Miles: ♪ Like tomorrow
doesn't exist ♪

01:50.443 --> 01:52.512
Why does my echo
sound better than me?

01:52.612 --> 01:53.913
♪ Exist ♪

01:53.980 --> 01:57.417
♪ I'm gonna fly ♪

01:57.484 --> 02:00.153
♪ Like a bird
from the night ♪

02:00.253 --> 02:01.354
Oh, my God.

02:01.454 --> 02:03.289
Miles,
you have to audition

02:03.356 --> 02:04.757
for Mr. Escalante's
musical.

02:04.824 --> 02:06.359
I'm more of a sing-in-the-shower
kind of guy.

02:06.459 --> 02:08.461
[ Gasps ] You should shower
in front the whole world.

02:08.528 --> 02:09.596
What?

02:09.662 --> 02:11.598
I'm pretty sure
I'm supposed to be

02:11.664 --> 02:13.700
helping you reach
your full potential.

02:13.800 --> 02:15.869
You shouldn't hide that talent.
Come on. What do you say?

02:15.969 --> 02:17.937
You're gonna keep pressuring me
until I audition, right?

02:18.004 --> 02:19.873
You're really
getting to know me.

02:19.973 --> 02:21.508
I will not stop.

02:21.608 --> 02:23.176
I guess
it'd be kind of cool.

02:23.276 --> 02:27.547
Yes,
another win for Alicia.

02:27.647 --> 02:29.949
You know, this calls for
a celebratory duet.

02:30.016 --> 02:31.351
From the top.

02:31.451 --> 02:34.554
♪ I'm gonna swing ♪

02:34.654 --> 02:36.689
Miss G!

02:36.789 --> 02:39.058
Can you keep it down?
It's my free period,

02:39.159 --> 02:41.794
and I'm trying
to watch my stories.

02:43.997 --> 02:48.401
♪♪

02:48.501 --> 02:49.636
So, as you know,

02:49.702 --> 02:51.237
I made an app
that rates your status updates

02:51.337 --> 02:52.472
before they go out

02:52.539 --> 02:54.807
as good, problematic,
or don't do it,

02:54.874 --> 02:57.043
but I -- [chuckles]
I think it's broken

02:57.143 --> 02:58.845
because every time
I use it,

02:58.912 --> 03:01.514
it keeps saying,
"Problematic."

03:01.581 --> 03:04.050
Hey, Sarah, uh,
quick question.

03:04.150 --> 03:06.252
Are you free tomorrow
after swim practice?

03:06.352 --> 03:07.854
Well, I was gonna
rearrange the letters

03:07.921 --> 03:09.756
on the school marquee
into a series of curse words.

03:09.856 --> 03:11.591
You know,
girl stuff.

03:11.691 --> 03:12.892
[ Chuckles ] Cool.

03:12.992 --> 03:14.894
Um, I was just wondering
if you were interested

03:14.994 --> 03:17.497
in hanging,
maybe over coffee?

03:17.564 --> 03:19.098
Yeah,
I'd really like that.

03:19.199 --> 03:20.900
I'll see
you all later.

03:22.168 --> 03:23.570
Dude!

03:23.670 --> 03:26.539
You finally set a time with her,
one-on-one.

03:26.606 --> 03:28.508
Um, chest bump.

03:28.575 --> 03:31.711
You know, touching fronts
is not as cool as you think.

03:31.778 --> 03:33.947
What? You're not happy
for Terrell?

03:34.047 --> 03:36.049
No, I totally am.
I never said that.

03:36.115 --> 03:37.350
It's just, uh,

03:37.417 --> 03:39.786
Sarah clearly thinks
you asked her to a group hang.

03:39.886 --> 03:42.722
She said, "I'll see you all
later at the coffee shop."

03:42.789 --> 03:44.123
No, no, no,
no, no, no.

03:44.224 --> 03:46.626
She said, "I will see
you all later,"

03:46.726 --> 03:49.295
meaning, "I will see you
around school,

03:49.395 --> 03:51.364
but I will
see you, Terrell,

03:51.431 --> 03:53.633
for our romantic
one-on-one."

03:53.733 --> 03:56.803
As a man who's paid his dues
on the dating scene,

03:56.903 --> 03:59.639
I think I know.

03:59.739 --> 04:02.208
She said,
knowing full well.

04:02.275 --> 04:04.310
[ Chuckles ]
No, no, seriously. Who?

04:04.410 --> 04:07.480
Um, Robyn,
in the sixth grade.

04:07.580 --> 04:09.315
[ Scoffs ]
Everybody knows that.

04:09.415 --> 04:10.984
We spent the afternoon
at my house

04:11.084 --> 04:12.252
because your mom forgot

04:12.318 --> 04:14.120
to pick you up
from my birthday party.

04:15.221 --> 04:17.790
That is not
a relationship.

04:17.890 --> 04:19.292
For the record,
people told me

04:19.392 --> 04:21.661
you spent the whole party
asking where I was.

04:21.761 --> 04:23.663
Because we were playing
hide and seek.

04:23.763 --> 04:25.832
Yeah, okay, well,
you just tell yourself

04:25.932 --> 04:27.500
whatever it is
you need to hear.

04:27.600 --> 04:30.336
I'm sorry to bring our baggage
into this.

04:30.436 --> 04:31.571
Bro,
what baggage?

04:31.638 --> 04:33.273
There is no --
it ceased to exist.

04:33.339 --> 04:35.942
Guys, guys, guys, if I was
interested in old drama,

04:36.009 --> 04:39.345
I'd watch "One Tree Hill"
with my cousins.

04:39.445 --> 04:41.014
I need to know
what to prepare for --

04:41.114 --> 04:42.315
a hang
or a group hang.

04:42.415 --> 04:43.616
The first.

04:43.683 --> 04:45.952
Okay, I hear
what you're saying,

04:46.019 --> 04:48.087
but I like
what he's saying.

04:48.154 --> 04:49.355
As much
as I can't believe

04:49.455 --> 04:51.858
these words are about
to come out of my mouth,

04:51.958 --> 04:53.026
I got to go
with Luke.

04:53.126 --> 04:56.162
[ Chuckles ]
Excellent choice, my friend.

04:56.262 --> 04:57.363
Chest bump.

04:57.463 --> 04:59.432
Yeah.
Come on.

05:01.668 --> 05:04.370
It was too much bump,
not enough chest.

05:04.470 --> 05:09.008
♪♪

05:09.108 --> 05:11.444
Okay.
My assistant director.

05:11.511 --> 05:13.046
Show me my spaceship.

05:13.146 --> 05:15.214
I think you're gonna be
pretty happy.

05:15.315 --> 05:17.884
Oh, uh, for safety,
just...

05:22.455 --> 05:26.626
So I'm still working out
some of the kinks.

05:26.693 --> 05:27.860
What's wrong?

05:27.960 --> 05:29.729
Nothing. [ Chuckles ]

05:29.829 --> 05:31.664
I guess
in my mind,

05:31.731 --> 05:33.900
this isn't just,
like, a spaceship.

05:34.000 --> 05:36.703
It's, like, a vessel powered by
the hopes and dreams

05:36.803 --> 05:38.204
of two lost alien souls

05:38.304 --> 05:40.573
and their 25
respective hearts.

05:40.673 --> 05:44.410
Um, just remember
the budget was $50.

05:45.345 --> 05:46.813
Anyway,
you know what?

05:46.879 --> 05:48.548
We'll make this work.

05:48.648 --> 05:51.584
Oh, we'll make this work.
Because it's that bad.

05:51.684 --> 05:54.354
Hey, I did not say that.
This is a good job.

05:54.420 --> 05:56.255
I'm gonna make
the greatest alien spaceship

05:56.356 --> 05:59.158
your stupid eyes
have ever seen.

05:59.225 --> 06:00.393
Thank you?

06:00.493 --> 06:02.562
Hi, Makayla.
Okay.

06:03.696 --> 06:05.898
Elliot,
call an OB-GYN

06:05.998 --> 06:07.700
'cause a star
is about to be born.

06:07.767 --> 06:10.269
For the last time,
teachers can't be in the play.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.372
Not me.

06:12.438 --> 06:14.173
But thank you.

06:14.240 --> 06:16.609
Meet your new star.

06:16.709 --> 06:17.877
Hey,
Mr. Escalante.

06:17.944 --> 06:19.545
Hey, Miles.
Miles can sing?

06:19.612 --> 06:21.447
Does my mother
have an opinion on my hair?

06:22.281 --> 06:23.216
Yes.

06:24.851 --> 06:26.386
Miles,
show him.

06:26.452 --> 06:27.754
Hold it right there.

06:27.854 --> 06:29.455
Griffin!
Get in here.

06:29.555 --> 06:31.090
I just cast Griffin
this morning.

06:31.190 --> 06:33.793
Uh, he'd be playing your
love interest, so sing to him.

06:33.893 --> 06:35.928
I want you
to really sell me.

06:36.028 --> 06:37.196
Good luck, Niles.

06:37.263 --> 06:39.265
[ Chuckles nervously ]
It's actually...

06:39.365 --> 06:41.601
No, you know what?
Niles works.

06:41.701 --> 06:42.969
He really
wants to do this.

06:43.069 --> 06:44.771
Okay, love that you're
looking out for him,

06:44.871 --> 06:46.439
but this
is the big time.

06:46.539 --> 06:47.874
It's clearly not.

06:47.940 --> 06:49.609
[ Soft music playing ]

06:49.709 --> 06:52.245
One, two, three...

06:52.311 --> 06:55.882
♪♪

06:55.948 --> 06:58.217
He's -- He's just nervous
I can fix it.

06:58.284 --> 07:01.621
Um, hey, just pretend
we're in the bathroom together.

07:01.721 --> 07:05.124
♪♪

07:05.224 --> 07:06.292
Miles, wait.

07:06.392 --> 07:08.261
Before you think
that's weird,

07:08.327 --> 07:10.463
Terrell was there, too.

07:10.563 --> 07:16.335
♪♪

07:16.436 --> 07:19.005
Sarah is gonna
love you,

07:19.105 --> 07:21.140
but you should
really reconsider

07:21.240 --> 07:23.309
that finishing touch
I suggested.

07:23.409 --> 07:26.145
The monocle?
Do I look like Mr. Monopoly?

07:26.245 --> 07:28.614
This is the guy
you choose to listen to.

07:29.482 --> 07:31.517
Terrell, I'm telling you,
this is a mistake.

07:31.617 --> 07:33.352
She doesn't think
this is a date.

07:33.453 --> 07:35.588
Okay, well,
we're about to find out

07:35.655 --> 07:38.524
who is right
and who is -- wrong!

07:38.624 --> 07:39.859
Oh,
I was so wrong.

07:39.959 --> 07:41.828
She is not
dressed for a date.

07:41.928 --> 07:43.529
No!

07:43.629 --> 07:46.265
Guys, my outfit
has romance written all over it.

07:46.332 --> 07:48.668
What do I do?

07:48.768 --> 07:51.137
How does stripping
help me?

07:51.204 --> 07:54.207
You're practically naked
in the pool every day.

07:55.641 --> 07:57.176
Uh, yeah, Luke,
go run interference.

07:57.276 --> 07:59.679
Terrell, I got you, okay?

08:01.981 --> 08:03.549
Hi, Luke.

08:03.649 --> 08:04.717
What are you doing?

08:04.817 --> 08:07.286
I'm...
thinking of a letter.

08:07.353 --> 08:09.722
Guess what it is.

08:09.822 --> 08:11.290
[ Imitates buzzer ]

08:11.357 --> 08:13.726
The correct answer
was "H."

08:13.826 --> 08:14.961
Think of another one.

08:15.027 --> 08:16.562
Are --

08:16.662 --> 08:17.864
Let me finish.

08:17.964 --> 08:20.399
Are you an idiot?

08:20.500 --> 08:22.635
Terrell!

08:22.702 --> 08:25.137
Now think of a number.
No, no.

08:25.204 --> 08:27.173
Hey, Sarah.

08:27.240 --> 08:28.407
Welcome to
the group hang,

08:28.508 --> 08:29.909
where we all hang
as a group.

08:30.009 --> 08:31.077
[ Chuckles ]

08:31.177 --> 08:34.914
Wow, that is --
that is one fitted...

08:35.014 --> 08:36.082
flannel.

08:36.182 --> 08:37.984
It's a Canadian large.

08:38.050 --> 08:40.419
The sizes don't really
translate overseas.

08:40.520 --> 08:44.190
♪ I like that, yeah ♪

08:44.257 --> 08:46.759
♪ I like that ♪

08:46.859 --> 08:49.228
When I petitioned
for a gender-neutral bathroom,

08:49.328 --> 08:51.264
this isn't
what I had in mind.

08:51.364 --> 08:52.765
What happened yesterday?

08:52.865 --> 08:55.768
I don't know if you realize,
but you didn't sing.

08:55.868 --> 08:57.003
Like at all.

08:57.069 --> 08:58.871
The stupid play
isn't for me, okay?

08:58.938 --> 09:01.073
There's no reason to be scared
of Mr. Escalante.

09:01.173 --> 09:03.042
He is not
a real director.

09:03.109 --> 09:05.077
Yeah,
but I'm not scared of<i> him.</i>

09:05.177 --> 09:06.445
I forgot how to human
when I discovered

09:06.546 --> 09:08.114
I was auditioning
as the love interest

09:08.214 --> 09:09.582
of<i> the</i> Griffin.

09:09.682 --> 09:11.951
So?
What's so great about Griffin?

09:12.051 --> 09:14.120
You're joking, right?
He's smart,

09:14.220 --> 09:16.622
he's funny, and he looks like
a hot teen vampire,

09:16.722 --> 09:19.926
but without
all the teen-vampire drama.

09:20.026 --> 09:22.295
I get it.
You like Griffin.

09:22.395 --> 09:24.530
Obviously.
Everyone likes Griffin.

09:24.597 --> 09:27.967
Okay, so you get to play
opposite him in a musical.

09:28.067 --> 09:30.102
Dude,
that's great.

09:30.202 --> 09:31.938
All due respect,
Ms. Gomez,

09:32.038 --> 09:33.639
but you're
out of your element,

09:33.739 --> 09:35.975
Griffin could have any guy
he wants at this school.

09:36.075 --> 09:38.044
There's no way
he'd choose me.

09:38.110 --> 09:40.313
Ugh.

09:40.413 --> 09:42.882
Miles,
don't sell yourself short.

09:42.949 --> 09:45.151
We've all been there.

09:45.251 --> 09:46.485
We've all
been forced to sing

09:46.586 --> 09:48.988
in an alien musical
with our crush?

09:49.088 --> 09:50.323
Look...

09:50.423 --> 09:52.425
when I was
in high school,

09:52.491 --> 09:55.895
I was madly in love with
this gorgeous senior named Jake,

09:55.962 --> 09:57.964
and on my 16th birthday,
which my dad forgot,

09:58.064 --> 09:59.498
he found out I liked him
and --

09:59.599 --> 10:00.833
And he pulled up
in his red Porsche

10:00.933 --> 10:02.134
after a school bus
pulled away.

10:02.234 --> 10:04.837
I've seen
"Sixteen Candles."

10:04.937 --> 10:06.772
Damn you
for being an old soul.

10:06.839 --> 10:08.140
I mean, really,
who knows

10:08.240 --> 10:10.009
how many opportunities
I've lost out on

10:10.109 --> 10:13.913
'cause I was scared --
roller coasters, getting bangs,

10:13.980 --> 10:16.248
going in the drive-thru
at 1:00 a.m.

10:16.315 --> 10:18.351
You could still do
all those things.

10:18.451 --> 10:21.287
<i>You</i> could still do
the musical.

10:21.354 --> 10:22.521
It's true.

10:22.622 --> 10:24.190
I've always dreamed
of being in a musical.

10:24.290 --> 10:25.358
So what do I do?

10:25.458 --> 10:26.926
I mean,
I really blew that audition.

10:26.993 --> 10:28.494
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, you did.

10:29.362 --> 10:33.032
Don't worry. I got you.
I'll -- I'll think of something.

10:33.132 --> 10:34.367
Please don't.

10:34.467 --> 10:35.601
You're right!

10:35.668 --> 10:38.037
I'm better
when I wing it!

10:38.137 --> 10:40.172
♪♪

10:40.272 --> 10:42.475
My other spaceship's
a hybrid.

10:42.541 --> 10:43.609
So...

10:43.676 --> 10:45.478
Griffin,
no more ad-libbing.

10:45.544 --> 10:48.047
Elliot, you need to give Miles
another shot.

10:48.147 --> 10:49.448
I'd love to,
but clearly,

10:49.515 --> 10:51.183
this moment
is too big for him.

10:51.283 --> 10:52.718
The play
opens tomorrow,

10:52.818 --> 10:54.620
and no one else
has auditioned.

10:54.687 --> 10:56.155
He's got the part.

10:56.222 --> 10:57.289
Yes.

10:57.356 --> 10:59.158
You're not gonna
regret this.

10:59.225 --> 11:01.227
Oh, my God,
I'm his manager now.

11:01.327 --> 11:03.029
Do you pay me directly
or --

11:04.864 --> 11:06.365
Just Venmo me.

11:07.333 --> 11:09.301
I already regret this.

11:09.368 --> 11:13.406
♪♪

11:13.506 --> 11:18.511
[ Slurping ]

11:21.414 --> 11:23.182
[ Sighs ]

11:23.249 --> 11:26.385
Look at us, a bunch
of friends being friends,

11:26.485 --> 11:27.753
hanging out
at a coffee shop.

11:27.853 --> 11:30.589
It's like the show.
Um, uh...

11:30.690 --> 11:32.658
"Friends."

11:33.426 --> 11:36.228
Okay, uh, Robyn,
care to join me

11:36.328 --> 11:37.596
to get
some more coffee?

11:37.697 --> 11:40.266
[ Chuckles ]
Oh, thank God.

11:41.534 --> 11:44.070
Should've worn
the monocle.

11:45.538 --> 11:47.239
Hit me.

11:48.207 --> 11:49.709
Can you
keep a secret?

11:49.775 --> 11:51.444
"Keep" is
a strong word.

11:51.544 --> 11:52.945
When Terrell
invited me here,

11:53.045 --> 11:55.614
I kind of just thought
he meant the two of us.

11:55.715 --> 11:57.083
Oh.

11:57.183 --> 12:00.252
So like one on one,
like romantically.

12:00.352 --> 12:01.954
Yeah, I thought it was
pretty clear what he meant.

12:02.054 --> 12:05.391
I mean, I guess he just wanted
the cringe fest in there.

12:05.458 --> 12:07.059
[ Chuckles ]
You'd be surprised.

12:07.126 --> 12:09.695
Signals do get crossed
a lot.

12:09.762 --> 12:11.030
Yeah,
by idiots.

12:11.097 --> 12:13.132
Hey, let's not play
the blame game.

12:13.232 --> 12:16.035
Just give me
two seconds, please.

12:16.102 --> 12:19.572
Hey, guys,
so we have a situation.

12:19.638 --> 12:22.541
Sarah kind of
just wanted it to be a...

12:22.608 --> 12:24.610
[softly] one-on-one.

12:24.710 --> 12:25.945
What was that?

12:26.045 --> 12:27.313
[ Normal voice ] You know,
she wanted it to be

12:27.413 --> 12:29.949
her and Terrell and us,
just without us.

12:30.049 --> 12:32.218
Wait, so she wanted
what I wanted.

12:32.284 --> 12:34.820
And I was right
and you were wrong?

12:34.920 --> 12:36.622
And now
I've ruined my chances?

12:36.722 --> 12:39.325
This is a disaster.

12:39.425 --> 12:40.760
Luke is back,
baby!

12:40.826 --> 12:43.763
This calls for
an I-told-you-so selfie.

12:43.829 --> 12:46.065
[ Camera shutter clicks ]

12:46.132 --> 12:48.400
You send that to me
and I will hurt you.

12:48.467 --> 12:52.338
Can you guys please leave so
I can try to salvage this thing?

12:52.438 --> 12:54.607
[ Cellphone chimes ]

12:55.941 --> 12:58.177
I couldn't help myself.

12:58.277 --> 13:00.246
♪♪

13:00.312 --> 13:02.348
♪ Don't listen to a word I say ♪

13:02.448 --> 13:03.682
Stupid ship.

13:03.783 --> 13:05.584
I can't find
the parts to make it work.

13:05.651 --> 13:07.019
I know
you're a perfectionist,

13:07.119 --> 13:08.687
but you don't have to
obsess over this.

13:08.788 --> 13:11.490
You don't need to beg, borrow,
or steal to meet my vision.

13:11.590 --> 13:13.092
So you want me
to steal?

13:13.159 --> 13:15.027
I am 100%
not saying that.

13:15.127 --> 13:17.096
Blink if it's
a yes.

13:17.163 --> 13:18.631
I can't not blink,
Makayla.

13:18.697 --> 13:20.099
Copy that.

13:22.301 --> 13:25.437
Okay. Welcome, Miles,
to your first

13:25.504 --> 13:27.306
and our last rehearsal.

13:28.808 --> 13:30.876
Alright,
so in this scene,

13:30.976 --> 13:34.446
Zalien must tell Gorben-Glop
how he feels

13:34.513 --> 13:37.883
in the universal language
of the cosmos -- music.

13:37.983 --> 13:39.552
What is
this musical about?

13:39.652 --> 13:40.686
I don't know.

13:40.786 --> 13:43.222
I think we're making it up
on the fly.

13:43.322 --> 13:45.024
Cue the orchestra.

13:46.125 --> 13:47.293
[<i> Soft music plays</i> ]

13:47.359 --> 13:49.161
♪ The said
I couldn't do it ♪

13:49.228 --> 13:52.064
♪ But I'm flying next to you
and ♪

13:52.164 --> 13:57.303
♪ Getting further
from the ground below ♪

13:57.369 --> 14:00.139
♪ Different worlds
brought us together ♪

14:00.206 --> 14:02.908
♪ If I can survive
the weather ♪

14:03.008 --> 14:05.010
Wow,
you wrote this?

14:05.077 --> 14:08.414
Wrote?
It poured out of me.

14:08.514 --> 14:12.084
♪ I'll need your hand
to take me home ♪

14:12.184 --> 14:15.921
♪ I want to go
wherever you go ♪

14:16.021 --> 14:18.691
♪ And just lead me
to space ♪

14:18.757 --> 14:22.828
♪ We can face
what they throw at us ♪

14:22.895 --> 14:28.667
♪ Just don't let go ♪

14:28.734 --> 14:30.669
He is really good.

14:30.736 --> 14:32.238
I know.

14:32.338 --> 14:34.673
♪ I want to fly ♪

14:34.740 --> 14:35.908
Sing it to him.

14:36.008 --> 14:38.077
♪ I want to fly ♪

14:38.177 --> 14:40.913
♪ I want to fly,
take my hand and -- ♪

14:41.013 --> 14:42.348
I'm sorry.

14:42.414 --> 14:44.183
I can't do this.

14:44.250 --> 14:47.086
Mr. Escalante,
I quit.

14:50.556 --> 14:52.424
Told you
this was a mistake.

14:59.398 --> 15:03.035
Music has brought
this galaxy together.

15:03.102 --> 15:05.237
Let's rejoice!

15:05.304 --> 15:07.473
Drip Lord, out.

15:08.941 --> 15:11.310
♪♪

15:11.410 --> 15:14.213
Hey, Sarah, you took off
before we could talk.

15:14.280 --> 15:16.415
Oh, yeah,
I needed to add an "S"

15:16.482 --> 15:19.752
onto "As the World Sa-Turns"
on the school marquee.

15:19.818 --> 15:22.988
"Ass the World Sa-Turns."
I made it "Ass."

15:23.088 --> 15:24.423
[ Chuckles ]
Cool, cool.

15:24.490 --> 15:27.826
Look, the truth is
when I asked you to hang out,

15:27.927 --> 15:30.930
I was hoping
it would just be the two of us.

15:30.996 --> 15:32.564
Yeah, me too.

15:32.631 --> 15:34.099
I mean,
that was more awkward

15:34.166 --> 15:35.834
than when Mr. Escalante
went in for a handshake

15:35.935 --> 15:37.303
and Ms. Gomez
went in for a hug.

15:37.403 --> 15:39.638
[ Chuckles ]
Look, the truth is

15:39.738 --> 15:41.407
I let my friends
get in my head,

15:41.473 --> 15:42.641
which is why
from now on,

15:42.741 --> 15:44.410
I'm gonna be
as direct as possible.

15:44.476 --> 15:46.412
Cool.
I'm listening.

15:46.478 --> 15:48.180
Alright.

15:48.280 --> 15:49.982
Hanging.

15:50.082 --> 15:51.417
Musical.

15:51.483 --> 15:52.584
Solo.

15:52.651 --> 15:54.086
Yeah,
you feel me?

15:54.153 --> 15:56.155
Is that the most direct
you can be?

15:56.255 --> 15:57.823
Well, if it's so easy,
you try it.

15:57.923 --> 15:59.124
Sure, "Sarah,
I would love

15:59.191 --> 16:01.126
to go to the musical with you
one-on-one."

16:01.193 --> 16:03.162
I don't hear
a difference.

16:04.430 --> 16:06.365
Alright, well,
what do you say?

16:06.465 --> 16:07.599
I'd love to.

16:07.666 --> 16:10.102
[ Bell rings ]

16:14.807 --> 16:16.809
What's in the cart,
Makayla?

16:16.875 --> 16:18.210
Nothing.

16:18.310 --> 16:21.180
Definitely not stealing supplies
from the robotics lab

16:21.280 --> 16:22.848
to build
a sick-ass spaceship

16:22.948 --> 16:25.617
to rub
in Mr. Escalante's stupid face.

16:26.552 --> 16:28.721
I was never here.

16:28.821 --> 16:30.522
We're already gone.

16:31.390 --> 16:35.894
♪♪

16:35.995 --> 16:38.163
Miles,
are you okay?

16:38.230 --> 16:39.298
No.

16:39.365 --> 16:40.666
I told you Griffin
wasn't into me,

16:40.733 --> 16:43.535
and that rehearsal
just confirmed it.

16:44.169 --> 16:46.138
I'm sorry.

16:46.205 --> 16:47.840
I-I don't know what's
going through Griffin's head,

16:47.906 --> 16:51.210
but what I do know is that
you are an incredible singer.

16:52.011 --> 16:54.146
Game recognizes game.

16:54.213 --> 16:57.216
That last part really undermined
the compliment.

16:57.316 --> 16:59.018
Look, if Griffin
doesn't like you,

16:59.084 --> 17:00.319
that's too bad,

17:00.386 --> 17:02.421
'cause after the whole school
hears you sing,

17:02.521 --> 17:03.889
<i>you'll</i> be
out of<i> his</i> league.

17:03.989 --> 17:05.090
No one's gonna hear me

17:05.190 --> 17:06.425
if there's
no co-lead in the play.

17:06.525 --> 17:07.760
Alright,
we'll find another guy,

17:07.860 --> 17:09.161
or maybe I'll throw
some green paint on

17:09.228 --> 17:11.263
and see
where the music takes me.

17:11.363 --> 17:13.699
I'll find
another student.

17:13.766 --> 17:16.568
No need.
It's time I stood up for myself.

17:16.668 --> 17:21.907
♪♪

17:22.007 --> 17:24.176
Hey.

17:24.243 --> 17:26.445
You can't quit a musical
the night before it goes on.

17:26.545 --> 17:29.348
You made a commitment,
so if you have an issue with me

17:29.415 --> 17:31.917
or whatever,
let's just get it over with.

17:32.017 --> 17:34.119
Who says I have
an issue with you?

17:34.219 --> 17:36.855
It's obvious
because you're like...

17:36.922 --> 17:38.357
Griffin!

17:38.424 --> 17:40.592
And I'm like...
Miles.

17:42.061 --> 17:44.129
Yeah,
you're like Miles,

17:44.229 --> 17:48.367
the guy with one of the most
amazing voices I've ever heard.

17:49.234 --> 17:51.970
I was nervous just to be
onstage with you.

17:52.071 --> 17:54.073
What?!

17:54.139 --> 17:56.475
Yeah, I mean,
you've got it all --

17:56.575 --> 17:59.078
an undeniable talent...

17:59.144 --> 18:00.446
great look.

18:00.546 --> 18:02.047
What?!

18:04.083 --> 18:05.484
I guess I do.

18:05.584 --> 18:08.620
To be honest, I was nervous
to be around you, too.

18:08.720 --> 18:10.155
Really?

18:10.255 --> 18:13.158
But I pushed through
because, together, we'd be epic.

18:13.258 --> 18:15.961
Not to mention
the hottest alien couple.

18:16.061 --> 18:17.763
What?!

18:17.830 --> 18:19.832
I'm sorry. It was so much cuter
when you did it.

18:21.433 --> 18:22.601
I've --I'm in.
[ Chuckles ]

18:22.668 --> 18:24.770
Luke:
Where is he?

18:24.837 --> 18:26.138
You!

18:26.238 --> 18:29.108
Ooh, if you think you're
too good for my best friend,

18:29.174 --> 18:30.309
think again.

18:30.409 --> 18:32.911
You're about
to get Luked.

18:34.680 --> 18:38.117
Actually,
it's all good.

18:38.183 --> 18:39.985
Then why --
why did you text me

18:40.085 --> 18:42.020
that the prettiest people
do the ugliest things?

18:42.121 --> 18:43.422
Mnh-mnh.

18:43.489 --> 18:45.524
And this is my cue
to take him away.

18:45.624 --> 18:46.859
Gentlemen.

18:46.959 --> 18:49.361
Get Luked?
Really?

18:49.461 --> 18:57.336
♪♪

18:57.436 --> 19:01.974
[ Applause ]

19:02.040 --> 19:04.276
Good evening,
Meadows Creek High.

19:04.343 --> 19:05.811
Well, I hope
all you theater lovers

19:05.878 --> 19:09.982
enjoy our production
of "As the World Sa-Turns."

19:10.048 --> 19:14.319
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:14.386 --> 19:20.058
♪ I want to fly ♪

19:20.159 --> 19:21.627
♪ I want to fly ♪

19:21.693 --> 19:25.864
♪ Take my hand
and I'll fly with you ♪

19:25.964 --> 19:31.336
♪ I'm gonna fly ♪

19:31.403 --> 19:33.038
♪ Look at me fly ♪

19:33.138 --> 19:37.075
♪ But just don't
let go too soon ♪

19:37.176 --> 19:39.912
♪ 'Cause they can't
bring us back down ♪

19:40.012 --> 19:46.218
♪ When our feet
are touching the moon ♪

19:46.318 --> 19:50.589
[ Cheers and applause ]

19:50.689 --> 19:54.059
Come, Zalien,
let's run away to my spaceship.

19:54.159 --> 19:56.061
Oh, Gorben-Glop,

19:56.161 --> 19:58.664
my 25 hearts
beat only for you.

19:58.730 --> 20:02.067
[ Cheers and applause ]

20:02.167 --> 20:08.941
♪♪

20:09.041 --> 20:10.108
[ Sighs ]

20:10.209 --> 20:12.611
Come on, Makayla,
you got this.

20:12.711 --> 20:17.783
♪♪

20:17.883 --> 20:19.218
I did it.

20:19.284 --> 20:21.353
I can't believe it worked.

20:21.420 --> 20:22.854
♪♪

20:25.724 --> 20:27.292
Oh, balls.

20:27.392 --> 20:35.200
♪♪

20:35.267 --> 20:36.969
I cannot believe
you blew the power

20:37.069 --> 20:38.971
for the entire East Bay.

20:39.071 --> 20:40.372
Pretty cool,
right?

20:40.439 --> 20:41.573
Totally.

20:41.640 --> 20:43.642
I need
to step up my game.

20:43.742 --> 20:45.611
I'm really
glad you changed your mind

20:45.711 --> 20:47.145
about doing
the musical.

20:47.246 --> 20:50.482
I had a lot of fun,
thanks to you.

20:50.582 --> 20:53.752
Me, too, Gorben-Glop.

20:53.819 --> 20:55.287
We should hang sometime.

20:55.387 --> 20:57.889
What?!

20:57.956 --> 21:00.125
Okay.

21:00.225 --> 21:03.161
Dude,
what a wild week.

21:03.262 --> 21:06.498
I mean, first,
I almost Luked Griffin,

21:06.598 --> 21:09.668
and now he wants to have
a group hang with us.

21:09.768 --> 21:12.337
[ Chuckles ] Bro,
that was clearly a one-on-one.

21:12.437 --> 21:14.172
No, no!
Don't listen to them!
